oai_dc:dc.dc:title: SCALE EFFECTS IN LARGE COASTAL MOBILE BED MODELS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Kamphuis, J.W.
Nairn, R.B.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: scale effects
bed model
movable bed
large model
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A series of mobile bed model tests of a prototype circular sand island was performed to determine scale effects. It was found that scale effect was largely a function of mobility number with some secondary effects of Reynolds number, bedform and critical profile depth. It was concluded that a model series using prototype sand grain size is necessary at this time to effect successful extrapolation to prototype.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 19 (1984): Proceedings of 19th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Houston, Texas, 1984.; 156
